==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Chryselephantine
<hw>Chrys`el*e*phan"tine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>chryso`s</grk> gold + <?/ made of ivory, fr. <?/ ivory,
elephant.]</ety> <def>Composed of, or adorned with, gold and
ivory.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The <xex>chryselephantine</xex> statues of the Greeks
were built up with inferior materials, veneered, as it were, with ivory
for the flesh, and gold decorated with color for the hair and
garments.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chrysene</ent>⟦br⟧
